{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nCompletion-verification is single-pass and, by contract, emits findings ONLY for FAILING\ncriteria (`reconcile_verdict` flips a PASS-with-findings to FAIL). On a PASS it persists just\nsigned counts via the attestation ‚Äî no per-criterion record exists anywhere, and the FAIL-only\nsidecar never fires. So a successfully-closed ticket has no durable per-criterion completion\naudit, unlike its plan and code reviews.\n\n## What\n\n1. Extend the verifier's output contract with a positive per-criterion `criteria[]` array ‚Äî one\n   `{criterion, met, citation, kind}` entry per acceptance/success criterion evaluated (met\n   status, a source-code or attestation citation, and its codebase-verifiable / operator-attested\n   kind). This rides ALONGSIDE the failures-only `findings`; a PASS keeps `findings == []`.\n2. Emit a completion sidecar on PASS (not only FAIL) persisting that array plus the verdict,\n   runner, model, and material fingerprint.\n\nCompletion stays single-pass ‚Äî this adds a per-criterion result list, NOT a four-pass structure.\n\n## The `kind` vocabulary (explicit, closed set)\n\n`kind` is the CLOSED two-value set `{\"codebase-verifiable\", \"operator-attested\"}`, matching ADR\n0043's two criterion kinds. `codebase-verifiable` means the verifier proved the criterion against\nreal code (its `citation` is a source-code location); `operator-attested` means the \"done\" evidence\nlives outside the codebase (a deploy, a live run, a console outcome) and the `citation` points at\nthe concrete attestation recorded on the ticket (a change URL/id, a vote/log/console outcome, a\ntimestamp). `met` is a bool.\n\n## Schema-version strategy (explicit)\n\nDo NOT bump the existing FAIL schema. Keep `SCHEMA = \"completion_verifier_fail_v1\"` unchanged (this\nis the actual constant name in `completion_sidecar.py` ‚Äî value `\"completion_verifier_fail_v1\"`), so\n`latest_fail_verdict` (which guards on `payload.get(\"schema\") == SCHEMA`) and the existing FAIL-record\ntests are untouched. Add a SECOND constant `SCHEMA_PASS = \"completion_verifier_pass_v1\"` for PASS\nrecords; `build_payload` picks the schema by verdict. This keeps\n`test_fail_close_persists_durable_verdict` and `test_pass_close_leaves_no_fail_record` green (a PASS\nrecord is a different schema, so `latest_fail_verdict` still returns None on a PASS).\n\n`citation` reuses the shared `Citation` shape (nullable).\n\n## Scope (enumerated edit targets)\n\n- `src/rebar/llm/contracts.py` ‚Äî **load-bearing**: `CompletionVerdict` (~lines 75-96) is a pydantic\n  `BaseModel` with no `extra=\"allow\"`, so pydantic v2 DROPS any `criteria[]` the agent emits unless\n  it is a declared field (the runner validates the LLM response against this model BEFORE reconcile\n  sees it, so a missing field is silently stripped). Add a `Criterion` sub-model\n  (`{criterion: str, met: bool, citation: Citation | None, kind: str}`) and a\n  `criteria: list[Criterion] = Field(default_factory=list)` field to `CompletionVerdict`.\n- `src/rebar/schemas/completion_verdict.schema.json` ‚Äî add the OPTIONAL `criteria[]` property\n  (items `{criterion, met, citation, kind}`); `findings` stays required, `criteria` optional. The\n  model‚Üîschema PARITY test\n  (`tests/interfaces/store/test_completion_verifier.py::test_completion_verdict_pins_to_schema`)\n  asserts the model's field set equals the schema's property set, so it MUST be UPDATED in lockstep\n  to include `criteria` (it will NOT pass unchanged) ‚Äî this is an expected, in-scope test edit.\n- `src/rebar/schemas/completion_reconcile_input.schema.json` ‚Äî **required because this schema is\n  `additionalProperties: false`**: add a `raw_criteria` (array) property, else the workflow's\n  `completion_reconcile` step would reject/not-carry the criteria. (The verify step's `criteria`\n  output must be threaded into the reconcile step ‚Äî see the YAML edit below.)\n- `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gates/completion-verification.yaml` ‚Äî in the `completion_reconcile`\n  step's `with:` (~lines 58-64), thread `raw_criteria: ${{ steps.verify.outputs.criteria }}`\n  (alongside the existing `raw_verdict`/`raw_findings`), so the agent's positive array reaches the\n  reconcile op.\n- `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_ops.py` ‚Äî `completion_reconcile(ctx)` (~lines 115-158) reads\n  `raw_criteria` from `ctx.inputs` and sets `result[\"criteria\"] = list(ctx.inputs.get(\"raw_criteria\")\n  or [])` on the reconciled verdict BEFORE `validate_structured`, so the workflow (close-gate) path\n  carries `criteria[]` end-to-end ‚Äî not only the bespoke `verify_completion` path.\n- `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/completion_verifier.md` ‚Äî update the prompt: instruct the agent to emit\n  `criteria[]` with one met-record per evaluated criterion. Specify per-entry that: `criterion` is\n  the criterion text; `met` is a **bool**; `kind` is drawn from the CLOSED vocabulary\n  `{codebase-verifiable, operator-attested}` (define both, per the section above); and a criterion\n  `citation` (singular ‚Äî the positive evidence that THIS criterion is met, a source-code location or\n  a recorded operator attestation) is DISTINCT from a finding's `citations` (plural ‚Äî the evidence a\n  FAILING criterion cites). `findings` stays failures-only.\n- `src/rebar/llm/completion.py` ‚Äî `reconcile_verdict` must NOT flip a PASS that carries a\n  populated `criteria[]` but empty `findings` (it keys the flip on `findings`; ensure `criteria[]`\n  is threaded through and not stripped, and add the regression test).\n- `src/rebar/llm/completion_sidecar.py` ‚Äî the existing constant is named `SCHEMA` (value\n  `\"completion_verifier_fail_v1\"`; `latest_fail_verdict` guards on it ~line 133). Do NOT rename or\n  bump it (that would churn the FAIL reader + `test_fail_close_persists_durable_verdict`); keep\n  `SCHEMA` as the FAIL schema and ADD a second constant\n  `SCHEMA_PASS = \"completion_verifier_pass_v1\"`. `build_payload` branches on the verdict\n  (PASS ‚Üí `SCHEMA_PASS` + `criteria[]`; FAIL ‚Üí unchanged `SCHEMA` + `findings`); add\n  `latest_pass_record(ticket_id)` mirroring `latest_fail_verdict` but schema-guarded to\n  `SCHEMA_PASS`. `latest_fail_verdict` (guarded to `SCHEMA`) is untouched, so a PASS record is\n  invisible to it and the existing FAIL tests stay green.\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py` ‚Äî the PASS path (~lines 211-256; the FAIL branch's\n  best-effort `completion_sidecar.emit` is ~line 238) currently does NOT emit on PASS. On the PASS\n  path (after the verdict is confirmed PASS, before `_verdict_manifest` signs), add a best-effort\n  `completion_sidecar.emit(result, material=‚Ä¶, repo_root=repo_root)` mirroring the FAIL branch's\n  call + best-effort semantics (swallow its own errors ‚Äî persistence is observability, never\n  load-bearing on the close). Set `result.setdefault(\"ticket_id\", resolved_id)` first.\n\n## Compatibility & rollback\n\n`criteria[]` is OPTIONAL ‚Äî an older agent/response that omits it yields today's behavior (PASS\ncounts only), and the failures-only `findings` invariant is unchanged, so nothing regresses. The\nFAIL path/schema/reader are entirely untouched; the new `SCHEMA_PASS` is additive. No backfill.\nReverting stops the PASS-path emit and drops the field; existing FAIL records stay readable (their\nschema is untouched).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A completion PASS returns a `criteria[]` array with one met-record per evaluated criterion\n      and `findings` stays empty, and `reconcile_verdict` does NOT flip it to FAIL. Oracle: a unit\n      test on `reconcile_verdict` feeding a PASS verdict with a populated `criteria[]`, asserting it\n      is NOT flipped to FAIL and the array survives reconcile; plus a test that the\n      `CompletionVerdict` pydantic model round-trips `criteria[]` (proving it is not dropped by\n      pydantic validation).\n- [ ] A completion PASS emits a `completion_verifier_pass_v1` sidecar persisting the per-criterion\n      array, read back by `latest_pass_record`. Oracle: an integration test that closes a ticket\n      through the gate with a stub verifier returning the new PASS shape and asserts on the emitted\n      event JSON (via the real sidecar emit path), plus that `latest_pass_record` reads it back and\n      `latest_fail_verdict` returns None on the same ticket.\n- [ ] Live end-to-end: running the real completion verifier (`[agents]` extra + API key) on a\n      fixture ticket whose criteria are met produces a PASS with a populated `criteria[]`\n      persisted to the sidecar. Oracle: a live/E2E test exercising the real agent path, gated on\n      LLM availability (skipped with a recorded reason otherwise).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784075633558717001,"uuid":"015e0225-d14c-46e8-820f-ec269c6c4a75"}